ensions to World Heritage properties in Austria, Romania and Spain |publisher=Whc.unesco.org |date= |accessdate=2010-09-20}}</ref> | rowspan="8"| <ref name="unesco2">{{cite web|url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/598 |title=Churches of Moldavia - UNESCO World Heritage Centre |publisher=Whc.unesco.org |date= |accessdate=2010-09-20}}</ref> |- | [[File:Biserica Manastirii Humorului si Turnul lui Vasile Lupu.jpg|100px]] | [[Humor Monastery|Humor]] |- | [[File:Mănăstirea Moldovița vedere laterala 2.jpg|100px]] | [[Moldovița Monastery|Moldovița]] |- | [[File:Biserica Inaltarea Sf. Cruci din Patrauti19.jpg|100px]] | [[Pătrăuți]] |- | [[File:RO SV Probota monastery ensemble 2.jpg|100px]] | [[Probota, Suceava|Probota]] |- | [[File:Mănăstirea Sfântul Ioan cel Nou26.jpg|100px]] | [[Suceava]] |- | [[File:Mănăstirea Voroneț vedere laterala 09.jpg|100px]] | [[Voroneț]] |- | [[File:Biserica si curtea manastirii Sucevita.jpg|100px]] | [[Sucevița Monastery|Sucevița]] |- | rowspan="6"| [[Dacian Fortresses of the Orăștie Mountains]] |[[File:Sarmizegetusa Regia 16.JPG|100px]] |[[Sarmizegetusa Regia]] | rowspan="5"| [[Hunedoara County|Hunedoara]] | rowspan="6"| {{hs|001}}1st centuries B.C. and A.D. | rowspan="6"| {{sort|0906|906; 1999; ii, iii, iv}} | rowspan="6"| An unusual fusion of military and religious architectural techniques and concepts. Including: *[[Sarmizegetusa Regia]], the capital of [[Dacia]]. *[[Costești-Cetățuie Dacian fortress]] *[[Costești-Blidaru Dacian fortress]], the strongest of the Dacian Fortresses. *[[Piatra Roșie Dacian fortress]]. *[[Dacian fortress of Bănița]]. *[[Dacian fortress of Căpâlna]]. | rowspan="6"| <ref name="unesco4">{{cite web|url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/906 |title=Dacian Fortresses of the Orastie Mountains - UNESCO World Heritage Centre |publisher=Whc.unesco.org |date=1999-12-02 |accessdate=2010-09-20}}</ref> |- | [[File:Costesti Cetatuie Dacian Fortress 2011 - Tower House One and Stairs-4.jpg|100px]] | [[Orăștioara de Sus|Costești-Cetățuie]]