aile Herculane .- Parc National vallée de la Cerna-Domogled..jpg|100px]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Domogled-Valea Cernei National Park|Domogled-Valea Cernei]] |- | style="background:#cfc;" | [[File:Cozia National Park, Romania.jpg|100px]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Cozia National Park|Cozia Massif]] | style="background:#cfc;" rowspan="2" | [[Vâlcea County|Vâlcea]] |- | style="background:#cfc;" | [[File:Casute pe culmea Runculet - panoramio.jpg|100px]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Lotru Mountains]] |- | style="background:#cfc;" | | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Șinca|Șinca Secular Forest]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Brașov County|Brașov]] |- | style="background:#cfc;" | [[File:Karpatenlandschaft bei Slatioara.JPG|100px]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Stulpicani|Slătioara Secular Forest]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Suceava County|Suceava]] |- | style="background:#cfc;" | [[File:Tibles Mountains from Pietrosul.jpg|100px]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Țibleș Mountains]] | style="background:#cfc;" | [[Maramureș County|Maramureș]] |- | [[Monastery of Horezu]] | [[File:Horezu H03-45.jpg|100px]] | [[Horezu]] | [[Vâlcea County|Vâlcea]] | {{hs|017}}1690 | {{sort|0597|597; 1993; ii}} | A masterpiece of the Brâncovenesc style | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/597 |title=Monastery of Horezu - UNESCO World Heritage Centre |publisher=Whc.unesco.org |date= |accessdate=2010-09-20}}</ref> |- | rowspan="7"| [[Villages with fortified churches in Transylvania]] | [[File:Biertan - panoramio (1).jpg|100px]] | [[Biertan]] | [[Sibiu County|Sibiu]] | rowspan="7"| {{hs|013}}13th to the 16th century | rowspan="7"| {{sort|0596|596; 1993, 1999 (extended); iv}} | rowspan="7"| A picture of the cultural landscape of southern Transylvania. Including: * The site of [[Biertan]] with the fortified church and a part of the town. *Village of [[Câlnic, Alba|Câlnic]]. *Village of [[Dârjiu]]. *Village of [[Prejmer]]. *Village of [[Saschiz]]. *Village of [[Valea Viilor]